Half Point?
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fswiss\fcharset0 Tahoma;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par '\b Half point\b0 ' is used in two situations.
\par \lang1033\f1 First,\lang1042\f0  when we talk about komi\lang1033\f1 ;\lang1042\f0  we say 6 and half points, or 5 and half points. The other case is when we talk about the \lang1033\b\f1 value\lang1042\f0  of a pae \b0 in the endgame.
\par
\par \lang1033\f1 T\lang1042\f0 he \lang1033\f1 value\lang1042\f0  of th\lang1033\f1 e\lang1042\f0  pae\lang1033\f1  at A\lang1042\f0  is\lang1033\f1  said to be worth\lang1042\f0  half a point, but \lang1033\f1 when strongly considered, we find that this\lang1042\f0  is not true.
\par
\par }
