Dia. 04 Not Half Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fswiss\fcharset0 Tahoma;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par If it is Black's turn, it is enough to play one move at \'a1\'e3.
\par If it is White's turn, he has to play two moves. (take and connect)
\par All together they need three moves to try to make 1 point.
\par Therefore each move \lang1033\f1 is worth\lang1042\f0  \cf1\b 1/3 points\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par \lang1033\f1 Therefore,\lang1042\f0  this pae \lang1033\f1 is worth precisely\lang1042\f0  1/3 points.
\par However\lang1033\f1 ,\lang1042\f0  it won't \lang1033\f1 affect a game\lang1042\f0  if someone understands \lang1033\f1 this\lang1042\f0  as half \lang1033\f1 a \lang1042\f0 point.
\par
\par }
